  "name": "RPlog_Fortune_Favors_The_Bold",
  "title": "Fortune Favors the Bold on Dathomir",
  "summary": "Eight days after a failed raid stranded both New Republic and Imperial forces on the hostile world of Dathomir, two scouting parties spot the same plume of smoke rising from a mountainside and set out to investigate, unaware of each other. Republic marine Lieutenant Wrista Ipex and Corporal Rook Sallowar climb light and silent, while Marshal Krieg leads a heavier-armored Imperial team in search of downed pilots. When an Imperial scout recklessly grenades a nest of fledgling fliers, the enraged mother creature kills him, and Wrista risks her own life to lure the predator away with mimicked cries, ultimately driving it off with sunlight reflected from her sword. At the summit cave, the parties converge to find an injured TIE pilot and the cheerful Squib X-wing pilot Barvareedee who saved him. Facing a rancor threat to the Imperial base camp, Wrista offers the Republic camp's shelter as a truce, and Krieg, choosing logic and survival over the war, agrees, the two commanders shaking hands as temporary allies.",
